cs.AR, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.ET, cs.SY 

The paper discusses the implementation of convolutional neural networks using computational memory, which falls under the categories of computer architecture (cs.AR), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), embedded systems (cs.ET), and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper specifically focuses on the communication fabric for the computational memory cores, which is a key aspect of computer architecture and embedded systems. Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of deep learning models, which falls under the categories of neural and evolutionary computing and computer vision and pattern recognition. Finally, the paper discusses the pipelined execution of these models, which falls under the categories of systems and control and computer architecture.
